# **D3 Analysis**

## **1\. System Description**

PlanIt addresses the problem of manual, back-and-forth appointment scheduling through phone, email, or paper calendars that affects small service providers such as photographers, barbers, and tutors. For small, appointment-driven businesses who currently coordinate bookings by hand, PlanIt is a web application for centralizing availability into a shareable link and lets clients self-schedule, unlike general-purpose tools like Google Calendar. Our product prevents conflicts with real-time availability checks, sends automated reminders, supports priority-ranked time slots, has a fast and simple UI for speedy, low-stakes signup times, and instantly syncs all available, booked, and edited time blocks with Google Calendar for personal calendar integration. The value proposition is to reduce manual scheduling time by up to 90% and prevent double-bookings for solo and micro-team service providers by giving them a centralized, shareable booking calendar with automated reminders.

The system allows **Business Owners** to create and manage their availability through **Availability Blocks** with different *priority\_levels*. Each **Business Owner** ***creates*** multiple **Booking Links** that can be shared with clients. **Clients** can ***access*** these links to view available time slots and ***make*** **Bookings** without creating accounts. The system ***sends*** **Notifications** for confirmations and reminders, and ***integrates*** with **Google Calendar** to sync all booking information.
